{{Infobox person | name = Nariman A. Irani | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Birth-date and age|Month DD, YYYY}} --> | birth_place = | death_date =December 10, 1977<!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = Mumbai | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = [[cinematographer]], [[film producer]] | known_for = ''[[Don (1978 film)|Don]]'' (1978) }}
'''Nariman A. Irani''' (? - December 10, 1977) was an [[Bollywood]] [[cinematographer]] and [[film producer]]. He is most known for producing ''[[Don (1978 film)|Don]]'' (1978) made under his banner Nariman Films and for his work as cinematographer in [[Chhailla Babu]](1977). He died in an accident, even before ''Don'' was even completed, eventually the film was a big hit and led to the [[Don (film series)|Don film franchise]].<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/oct/27zeenat.htm Zeenat: I think Vijay is missing] [[Rediff.com]], Movies, October 27, 2006.</ref><ref name=eco>{{cite news |title=Don 2 runs into legal maze by Nariman Films|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2011-11-12/news/30391224_1_nariman-films-legal-notice-big-films|publisher=The Economic Times |date= Nov 12, 2011 |accessdate=}}</ref>
As a cinematographer he is known for his films like ''Talash'', ''Saraswatichandra'' and ''[[Phool Aur Patthar]]'', ''[[Roti Kapada Aur Makaan]]''<ref name=eco/> and [[Chhailla Babu]]. He won the [[16th National Film Awards]] for [[National Film Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]] ([[Black-and-white|B & W]]) for ''[[Saraswatichandra (film)|Saraswatichandra]]'' (1968).,<ref name="16thaward">{{cite web|url=http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm16thNFAAward.aspx|title=16th National Film Awards|publisher=[[International Film Festival of India]]|accessdate= }}</ref><ref name="16thawardPDF">{{cite web|url=http://dff.nic.in/2011/16th_nff_1970.pdf|title=16th National Film Awards (PDF)|publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]]|accessdate= }}</ref> he also won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer]] in the same year.<ref>[http://deep750.googlepages.com/FilmfareAwards.pdf List of Filmfare Award Winners and Nominations, 1953–2005]</ref>
The cinematographer Nariman Irani, while working Chhailla Babu decided to borrow most of the plot of Chhailla Babu and shared a modified story idea to Chandra Barot,who made the new modified story as the film Don (1978). While ''Don'' was still under production, he was badly hurt, when after a sudden [[cloudburst]] in November 1977, a wall fell on him while he was preparing to take a shot for another film at [[Rajkamal Kalamandir]] studios, Mumbai during the making of Manojj Kumar's Kranti. A wall collapsed on him and he suffered a hip bone injury. Though he was hospitalised, but died a few days later.<ref name=eco/><ref>[http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/oct/16sld3.htm rediff.com: An exclusive interview with Chandra Barot, who made the first Don<!-- Bot generated title -->] Rediff.com, October 16, 2006.</ref>
==Legacy== His home banner Nariman Films was revived 18 years later by his sons, Nadir and Nadeem, with [[Suniel Shetty]]-starrer ''Shashtra'' (1996).<ref>{{cite news |title=Don producers make a comeback|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-11/news-interviews/29532121_1_producers-sanjay-dutt-comeback |publisher=The Times of India |date= May 11, 2011 |accessdate=Feb 8, 2013}}</ref>
