{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Paul Gillette | image = | caption = | birth_name= | birth_date = {{birth date|1938|10|01}}<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zMniAAAAMAAJ&dq=paul+1938 |title=Contemporary Authors: A Bio-bibliographical Guide to Current Writers in Fiction, General Nonfiction, Poetry, Journalism, Drama, Motion Pictures, Television and Other Field |page=193 |publisher=Gale Research Company|date= 1996 }}</ref> | birth_place = [[Carbondale, Pennsylvania]], US | death_date = {{death date and age|1996|1|6|1938|10|1}} | death_place = Los Angeles | occupation = Writer, wine expert | years_active = | alma_mater = [[Pennsylvania State University]] | spouse = Shelly Gillette | children = 2 daughters, Giuliana and Caroline | parents = | years active = | website = }} ''' Paul J. Gillette''' (October 1, 1938 – January 6, 1996) was an American wine expert and writer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/01/18/us/paul-gillette-58-wrote-play-misty.html |title=Paul Gillette, 58; wrote 'Play Misty'|date=January 18, 1996 |work=The New York Times }}</ref> He was among the first to host a nationally syndicated television show on wine appreciation, ''Enjoying Wine with Paul Gillette''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1996-01-17/local/me-25332_1_paul-gillette |title=Obituaries : Paul Gillette; Novelist, Wine Expert and Scriptwriter|work=[[LA Times]] |author=Daniel P. Puzo }}</ref> He was also known for writing ''Play Misty For Me'', the novelization of a script by [[Jo Heims]] and Dean Reisner for the [[Play Misty for Me|film of the same name]] starring [[Clint Eastwood]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_LLzAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT153#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Aim for the Heart: The Films of Clint Eastwood|author= Howard Hughes |publisher=I.B.Tauris|date=July 30, 2009|isbn=9780857730473 }}</ref>
